1. It get the imageboard from your json config. If you check the README.md you can see this example:
```
{"searches":[
    {
      "imageboard":"IMAGEBOARD",
      "folder_name":"YOUR_FOLDER_NAME",
      "board": "BOARD_LETTER",
      "keywords": ["KEYWORD1", "KEYWORD2"]
    },

    {
      "imageboard":"4chan",
      "folder_name":"vidya",
      "board": "v",
      "keywords": ["tf2", "splatoon", "world of tank"]
    }
]}
```

4scanner get the imageboard from ```"imageboard":"IMAGEBOARD"``` and default to 4chan if ```"imageboard":``` is missing from your search.

2. Yes, it only work on imageboards with a JSON API. (which is most imageboards)

