@indirectlylit I just tested 0.7.1-beta1 on Ubuntu 14.04. It shows that this problem still exists when running on Python 2. This is because the system Python 2 `OpenSSL` module's version is old. I also tested with Python 3 on the VM. In my VM, I don't have the system Python 3 `OpenSSL` module installed, so the problem doesn't exist. I think the fix for this issue is https://github.com/learningequality/kolibri/pull/2966, which is currently in the develop branch.

However, I just realize that removing the 64-bit linux cryptography makes the fix for this issue ineffective.
After removing the 64-bit cryptography: 
1. For Ubuntu 14.04, since `pyopenssl` [depends on `cryptography`](https://github.com/pyca/pyopenssl/blob/17.4.0/setup.py#L98) and `cryptography` is not installed in the system, then installing a higher version of `pyopenssl` will not fix the issue we have here when running in Python 2. If the users don't install the system Python 3 `OpenSSL`, then the issue won't show up. However, if they do, then the same issue will appear as it is in Python 2.
2. For Ubuntu 16.04+, we currently rely on the system module `cryptography 1.2.3`. However, the `pyopenssl` version `17.4.0` depends on `cryptography` > 1.9, so it will raise another error when we try to download content from Kolibri.

